Package: ggtikz
Title: Post-Process ggplots With TikZ Code Using Plot Coordinates
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Oliver",
           family = "Thomas",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "oliver.thomas@sgbm.uni-freiburg.de")
Description: Using tikzDevice, TikZ code can be exported from R. Base graphs can subsequently be modified using the tikzAnnotate function. grid.tikzAnnotate is available, but coordinates are hard to get to correspond to data coordinates for annotation of ggplots. ggtikz facilitates annotation of ggplot2 plots with arbitrary TikZ code, using absolute data or relative plot coordinates.
